    <item>
      <title>Using vi as a hex editor</title>
      <link>https://www.kevssite.com/using-vi-as-a-hex-editor/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2009 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.kevssite.com/using-vi-as-a-hex-editor/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes I find it useful to switch to hex mode when editing a file in vi. The command for switching is not very obvious so thought I&amp;rsquo;d share&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;So, open a file in vi as usual. To switch into hex mode hit escape and type:&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;:%!xxd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;And when your done and want to exit from hex mode hit escape again and type:&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;:%!xxd -r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Okay, so this isn&amp;rsquo;t actaully switching to vi&amp;rsquo;s &amp;lsquo;hex mode&amp;rsquo;; vi doesn&amp;rsquo;t have one. What the above actually does is to stream vi&amp;rsquo;s buffer through the external program &amp;lsquo;xxd&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
